	   <tr><td colspan=2>Heh Ishva Robe is +5 CHA, probably at least as good of a robe for Enchanters IF you need CHA, but most Enchanters at the levels you need to take her out are already at 200/200 INT/CHA.  But as a Mage I was happy to put this Robe on and take off my Ishva.  I get complimented all the time on the look, and I do hear it is her rare drop, in a dungeon most people overlook.  At 52 my Mage and Necro got full/partial resists on most of our spells, and I never got her Malosied.  From what I heard from the next party up their Shaman had trouble slowing her as well.  But not bad for an L51 MOB, the 10 weight is a REAL bummer though, between focus items and this robe I can't carry squat.  I was going to trade my 7 STR/INT neck for a mana one, but I don't think I can afford to at this point.  The Robe is also +10 MR, between the looks and the stats I'd take it over an FBCR any day, and it looks MUCH better.<br><br>And there's no way a party of people L50'ish is going to give a Robe to the Enchanter because it has +3 CHA.  And to the person that said they'd keep their BCR, that's because you haven't had a chance on it, even if for nothing else having one of the best looking Robes in the game is worth something, and stats are decent.  At L50 unless you play a really stupid class you're swapping INT gear for mana/resists anyways, so the higher INT robes aren't helping you that much.<br><br>And the Robe is her rarest drop.  That's why YOU'RE still in an Oracle Robe anonymous.  And her Necklace is +MANA as well as INT, every little bit helps.  She IS level 51 BTW.  The lowest level of the Dungeon is designed more for L20-30 players, and gets progressively harder.  At 52 we didn't hit blues regularly until the 6th Floor, and from then on it was pretty much all blue.  This is a progressive dungeon, and kind of a fun one too until you have to do CR : (  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
